===Etymology===
From {{der|en|ang|halh-gefeaxe|lit=grassy corner}}, compounded from {{compound|ang|healh|alt1=halh|feax|alt2=gefeaxe|nocat=1}}.
<ref>''Watts, Victor, The Cambridge Dictionary of English Place-Names'', 2010</ref> Folk etymology suggests {{der|en|ang|hāliġfeax|lit=holy hair}}, as compounded from {{compound|ang|halig|feax|nocat=1}}, from a local legend that the town is said to have received the name from the fact that the hair of a murdered virgin was hung up on a tree in the neighborhood, which became a resort of pilgrims. Compare also {{l|en|Fairfax}}.

